## §8 — Adding a new item

When new work surfaces:

1. Pick an ID prefix from your project's configured list. Common ones:
{{range .IDPrefixes}}   - `{{.}}-NNN`
{{end}}   Numbers are monotonic per-prefix. Look at the highest existing N + 1.
2. File: `.squad/items/<ID>-<kebab-title>.md`. Use the §9 template.
3. Frontmatter is mandatory. Body is short for routine items, longer for
   design-heavy ones.
4. If P0/P1, add to the Ready section of `.squad/STATUS.md`.
5. Commit: `git commit -am "docs: add <ID> <title>"`.

If the item is a half-baked thought, file it anyway with `priority: P3`
and `status: open`. Triage later.

